# Learn Polish - Interactive Language Learning Course 🇵🇱

*Witamy w Learn Polish!* / Welcome to Learn Polish!

An interactive web-based Polish language learning platform designed to help students master the Polish language through comprehensive exercises, grammar lessons, and vocabulary building activities.

## 🌟 Features

### Core Learning Modules
- *🔤 Verb Tenses*: Master present, past, and future tense conjugations
- *📚 Grammar & Cases*: Comprehensive coverage of Polish's 7 grammatical cases
- *🗣 Vocabulary Builder*: Extensive collection of 2,500+ Polish words with categories
- *🎯 Interactive Practice*: Dynamic exercises with immediate feedback
- *📖 Reference Materials*: Complete grammar guides and linguistic references
- *🃏 Flashcards*: Memory-based learning tools for vocabulary retention

### Interactive Features
- *Shuffle Mode*: Randomize exercises for varied practice sessions
- *Progress Tracking*: Monitor your learning progress and scores
- *Timer Function*: Timed exercises to improve response speed
- *Category Filtering*: Focus on specific topics (animals, colors, time, etc.)
- *Responsive Design*: Works seamlessly on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices

### Educational Content
- *Alphabet & Pronunciation*: Complete Polish alphabet with pronunciation guides
- *Numbers & Ordinals*: Cardinal and ordinal numbers with examples
- *Colors Reference*: Comprehensive color vocabulary
- *Calendar & Time*: Days, months, seasons, and time expressions
- *Common Verbs*: Most frequently used Polish verbs with conjugations
- *Pronouns*: Personal, possessive, and demonstrative pronouns
- *Prepositions*: Spatial and temporal prepositions with case requirements
- *Gender Rules*: Masculine, feminine, and neuter gender identification

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- No additional software installation required

### Installation
1. *Clone or Download*
   bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   # or download and extract the ZIP file
   

2. *Open the Application*
   - Navigate to the project folder
   - Open index.html in your web browser
   - Start learning immediately!

### File Structure

Polish-Course/
├── index.html              # Main landing page
├── LICENSE                 # MIT License
├── README.md              # This file
├── css/                   # Stylesheets
│   ├── common.css         # Shared styles
│   ├── navigation.css     # Navigation styling
│   ├── practice.css       # Exercise interface
│   └── [other css files] # Module-specific styles
├── data/                  # Learning content
│   ├── vocabulary.json    # 2500+ vocabulary entries
│   └── exercises.json     # Practice exercises
├── pages/                 # Learning modules
│   ├── present.html       # Present tense lessons
│   ├── past.html         # Past tense lessons
│   ├── future.html       # Future tense lessons
│   ├── cases.html        # Grammatical cases
│   ├── grammar.html      # Grammar & gender
│   ├── vocabulary.html   # Vocabulary builder
│   ├── practice.html     # Interactive exercises
│   └── references.html   # Reference materials
└── script/               # JavaScript functionality
    ├── common.js         # Shared utilities
    ├── practice.js       # Exercise engine
    ├── vocabulary.js     # Vocabulary management
    └── [other js files]  # Module-specific scripts


## 📖 How to Use

### 1. Choose Your Learning Path
- *Beginners*: Start with Present Tense → Vocabulary → Grammar
- *Intermediate*: Focus on Cases → Past/Future Tense → Practice Exercises
- *Advanced*: Use References → Practice Exercises → Custom vocabulary sets

### 2. Navigate the Platform
- Use the *navigation bar* to switch between modules
- Access the *sidebar* in References for quick topic jumping
- Use the *home button* to return to the main menu

### 3. Practice Exercises
- Select exercise type (Grammar, Numbers, Cases, Vocabulary, Flashcards)
- Enable *Shuffle Mode* for randomized questions
- Use the *Timer* to challenge yourself
- Track your *score* and progress

### 4. Vocabulary Learning
- Browse categories (animals, colors, time, etc.)
- Use *search functionality* to find specific words
- Practice with *flashcard mode*
- Load custom vocabulary sets

## 🎯 Learning Objectives

By completing this course, you will be able to:
- ✅ Conjugate Polish verbs in all major tenses
- ✅ Use the 7 Polish grammatical cases correctly
- ✅ Build a vocabulary of 2,500+ common Polish words
- ✅ Form grammatically correct sentences
- ✅ Understand Polish gender rules and agreements
- ✅ Navigate everyday conversations in Polish

## 🛠 Technical Details

### Technologies Used
- *Frontend*: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- *Data Format*: JSON for vocabulary and exercises
- *Styling*: Custom CSS with responsive design
- *Storage*: Local browser storage for progress tracking

### Browser Compatibility
- ✅ Chrome 60+
- ✅ Firefox 55+
- ✅ Safari 11+
- ✅ Edge 79+

### Performance Features
- Lightweight and fast-loading
- Offline capability (after initial load)
- Minimal dependencies
- Optimized for mobile devices

## 📱 Mobile Experience

The platform is fully responsive and optimized for mobile learning:
- Touch-friendly interface
- Swipe gestures for navigation
- Optimized typography for small screens
- Fast loading on mobile networks

## 🔧 Customization

### Adding Your Own Content

#### Custom Vocabulary
1. Edit data/vocabulary.json
2. Follow the existing format:
   json
   {
     "polish": "słowo",
     "english": "word",
     "category": "category_name"
   }
   

#### Custom Exercises
1. Edit data/exercises.json
2. Add to existing categories or create new ones
3. Follow the question/answer format

#### Styling Modifications
- Modify CSS files in the css/ directory
- Use common.css for global changes
- Module-specific styling in respective CSS files

